<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-1352] HttpHeaderFilterStrategy tries to filter out &quot;http.requestMethod&quot; but doesn&apos;t</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-1352</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I actually found this in 1.5.0, but a quick look in ViewVC indicates that it still happens in 1.6.0 and in the trunk.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HttpHeaderFilterStrategy uses String.toLowerCase on &quot;http.responseCode&quot; because of the capital C.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should also use toLowerCase on &quot;http.requestMethod&quot; because of the capital M, but it doesn&apos;t.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus the http.requestMethod header leaks into the HTTP protocol headers.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
